title: Former MPs spend up on travel
text:
Topix › Pacific Travel › Former MPs spend up on travel Former MPs spend up on travel Next Story Prev Story 1 hr ago Read more: Examiner 
Department of Finance reports reveal that through the Life Gold Pass scheme, former MPs spent more than $35,000 from January to December on domestic travel, while two MPs racked up more than $10,000 for severance travel. Former Labor Senator John Coates spent the most with his Life Gold Pass, claiming $7402 for travel for himself and family. Start the conversation, or Read more at Examiner.
